The post-commit and post-rewrite thin triggers ship as parallel installable copies under hooks/bin and hooks/git-hooks that implement one contract — resolve dispatcher.mjs relative to the script's real on-disk location, capture HEAD or the rewrite stdin before backgrounding, spawn the dispatcher detached, and exit 0 without propagating failures — which the git-hook-setup handbook section documents for installers.
